  "body": "I'm not sure whether this is an intentional or bug but, throwing an issue to discuss.\r\n\r\nWhat I expect after issuing the following command is that the _output_ JSON file should have an `bytecode` field in the `contracts:<NAME>` field. Notice that there is no `bytecode` field in the `contracts:Foo` level:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ npx hardhat export --export output.json\r\n\r\n$ cat output.json\r\n{\r\n  \"contracts\": {\r\n    \"Foo\": {\r\n      \"address\": \"<REDACTED>\",\r\n      \"abi\": [...]\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nFormat of `./artifacts/contracts/Foo.json` file is slightly different from _exported_ file.\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ cat ./artifacts/contracts/Foo.json\r\n{\r\n  \"_format\": \"hh-sol-artifact-1\",\r\n  \"contractName\": \"Foo\",\r\n  \"sourceName\": \"contracts/Foo.sol\",\r\n  \"abi\": [...],\r\n  \"bytecode\": \"...\",\r\n  \"linkReferences\": {},\r\n  \"deployedLinkReferences\": {}\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nBy running `export` command, I'm exporting the current deployment. I expect a `bytecode` field, so we can easily use the _exported_ file to migrate with `web3.js`. In the _actual_ scenario, I can not use this file directly since there is no byte code representation.\r\n\r\nAny thoughts?",
